sidue buildup can affect your washing machine&#8217;s performance. Detergent and fabric softener can leave residues. These steps will help you remove buildup:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<ol start=\"1\" class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Mix a solution of warm water and baking soda.<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Dip a cloth in the solution and scrub the tub.<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Pay attention to corners and edges.<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Rinse with warm water to remove the baking soda.<\/li>\n<\/ol>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large is-resized\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"1024\" height=\"536\" src=\"https:\/\/www.lifewaytrove.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/07\/washing-machine-tub-1024x536.jpg\" alt=\"washing machine tub\" class=\"wp-image-1898\" style=\"width:783px;height:auto\" srcset=\"https:\/\/www.lifewaytrove.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/07\/washing-machine-tub-1024x536.jpg 1024w, https:\/\/www.lifewaytrove.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/07\/washing-machine-tub-300x157.jpg 300w, https:\/\/www.lifewaytrove.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/07\/washing-machine-tub-768x402.jpg 768w, https:\/\/www.lifewaytrove.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/07\/washing-machine-tub-450x236.jpg 450w, https:\/\/www.lifewaytrove.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/07\/washing-machine-tub-780x408.jpg 780w, https:\/\/www.lifewaytrove.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/07\/washing-machine-tub.jpg 1200w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Using baking soda is effective for residue. It is a gentle abrasive and safe for your machine.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Here is a quick troubleshooting table for easy reference:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-table\"><table><tbody><tr><td><strong>Issue<\/strong><\/td><td><strong>Solution<\/strong><\/td><\/tr><tr><td>Persistent Odors<\/td><td>Run a hot cycle with vinegar.<\/td><\/tr><tr><td>Residue Buildup<\/td><td>Scrub with baking soda solution.<\/td><\/tr><\/tbody><\/table><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"frequently-asked-questions\"><strong>Frequently Asked Questions<\/strong><\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>How To Clean The Inside Of A Washing Machine Drum?<\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>To clean the inside of a<strong> <a href=\"https:\/\/www.lifewaytrove.com\/how-to-remove-bad-smell-from-washing-machine\/\">washing machine drum<\/a>,<\/strong> add white vinegar and baking soda. Run a hot water cycle. Wipe down the drum with a clean cloth. Leave the door open to air dry. Repeat monthly for optimal results.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>What Is The Best Thing To Clean Inside A Washing Machine?<\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>The best thing to clean inside a washing machine is a mixture of white vinegar and baking soda.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>How To Clean The Tub In A Washing Machine?<\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>How to clean washing machine tub is essential to mix equal parts water and vinegar, and run a hot water cycle. Wipe dry.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Is Bleach Or Vinegar Better To Clean A Washing Machine?<\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Bleach is better for disinfecting and removing mold. Vinegar excels at eliminating odors and mineral buildup. Use both for best results.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>How Often Should I Clean My Washing Machine?<\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>How to clean washing machine tub is essential once a month to prevent mold and odors.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>What Supplies Do I Need For Cleaning?<\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>You need white vinegar, baking soda, and a microfiber cloth for effective cleaning.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"conclusion\"><strong>Conclusion<\/strong><\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Regularly how to clean washing machine tub is essential to ensure it runs efficiently and lasts longer. A clean tub prevents mold and mildew buildup. Follow the steps outlined above for a fresh, odor-free washer. Your laundry will come out cleaner and smelling better.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Keep your washing machine in top condition with these simple maintenance tips.<\/p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt